#: src/SHELL_AUDIT.md:5
msgid ""
"Assessment of the V0.2.1 `stddsl::Shell` bundle against typical devops and "
"sysadmin workloads delivered as signed-and-encrypted `loop main` scripts. "
"The initial audit identified three priority gaps. All three have been closed "
"under V0.2.1; the bundle is now adequate for the daemon use case. A "
"subsequent review of the script-orchestration path found that `shell::arg`/"
"`arg_count` reported the host process argv rather than the script's own "
"arguments and that `shell::run` discarded captured stderr; both were "
"corrected under V0.2.1. This document records the current state, the "
"corrections, and the limitations that remain."
