#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:22
msgid "Activating strict signing"
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:24
msgid "Three knobs activate strict signing, in precedence order."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:26
msgid ""
"**`KELEUSMA_TRUSTED_KEYS_DIR` environment variable** points at a directory "
"of `*.pub` files. Each file holds a 32-byte Ed25519 verifying key."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:27
msgid ""
"**Platform-conventional directory**: `/etc/keleusma/trusted_keys` on Unix-"
"like systems, `%PROGRAMDATA%\\keleusma\\trusted_keys` on Windows. Used when "
"the environment variable is unset."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:28
msgid ""
"**`KELEUSMA_REQUIRE_SIGNED=1`** environment variable forces strict mode even "
"with an empty trust store. Fail-closed for everything."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:30
msgid ""
"Strict signing activates when the trust store is non-empty OR when the force-"
"strict variable is set."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:32
msgid ""
"Discovery is fail-closed. A malformed key file (wrong size, invalid Ed25519 "
"encoding) causes the CLI to refuse to start with a clear diagnostic. This "
"prevents partial-trust-list edge cases."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:34
msgid "Activating strict encryption"
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:36
msgid ""
"The encryption gate uses parallel mechanisms. Three knobs in precedence "
"order:"
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:38
msgid ""
"**`KELEUSMA_DECRYPTION_KEYS_DIR` environment variable** points at a "
"directory of `*.seed` files. Each file holds a 32-byte X25519 private key."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:39
msgid ""
"**Platform-conventional directory**: `/etc/keleusma/decryption_keys` on Unix-"
"like systems, `%PROGRAMDATA%\\keleusma\\decryption_keys` on Windows."
msgstr ""

#: src/SECURITY_POLICY.md:40
msgid ""
"**`KELEUSMA_REQUIRE_ENCRYPTED=1`** environment variable forces strict "
"encryption mode even with an empty decryption-key store."
